│ // simplifications taking place.                                                                                             │
│ assert((BestFactor.Width == LegacyVF.Width ||                                                                                │
│         planContainsAdditionalSimplifications(getPlanFor(BestFactor.Width),                                                  │
│                                               CostCtx, OrigLoop)) &&                                                         │
│        "VPlan cost model and legacy cost model disagreed");                                                                  │
│ ```                                                                                                                          │
│ This confirms my understanding. The problem is likely that one of the cost models is mis-evaluating the cost for this        │
│ specific loop on this specific target.                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ A common approach to fix such disagreements is to disable the VPlan-native path for the specific case that is causing the    │
│ discrepancy, falling back to the legacy cost model which is considered more stable. This can be done by adding a check in    │
│ `LoopVectorizationPlanner::buildVPlans`.                                                                                     │
