│ `select` instruction in the entry block makes the starting value of the induction variable, and thus the trip count,         │
│ dependent on a function argument.                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ I will add a check at the beginning of `LoopVectorizationPlanner::buildVPlans` to see if the loop has a non-constant trip    │
│ count. If it does, I will disable the VPlan-native path by setting `CostCtx.EnableVPlanNativePath = false;`. This will force │
│ the vectorizer to use the legacy cost model, avoiding the disagreement and the subsequent crash. This is a conservative fix, │
│ but it's safe and directly addresses the observed failure mode.                                                              │
